OL,4,CGambling: Poorer UK towns found to have
OL,5,Cthe most betting shops, study shows
OL,6, A fifth of all gambling premises in the
OL,7, UK are now located in the poorest areas
OL,8, of the country, new research has found.
OL,10,FBetting shops are ten times more likely
OL,11,Fto be found in deprived towns than in
OL,12,Faffluent areas, according to a study by
OL,13,Fthe University of Bristol.
OL,15,FThe areas with the highest number of
OL,16,Fbetting shops per capita included
OL,17,FGlasgow, Liverpool, London and
OL,18,FMiddlesbrough, the study found.
OL,20,FThis comes amid the government's
OL,21,Fongoing review of the Gambling Act.
